#. <section class="sutta" id="sn47.37"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn47.37:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 47"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 47"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn47.37:0.2"
msgid "4. Ananussutavagga"
msgstr "4. Not Learned From Anyone Else"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn47.37:0.3"
msgid "37. Chandasutta"
msgstr "37. Desire"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.37:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, satipaṭṭhānā."
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these four kinds of mindfulness meditation."

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.3"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.4"
msgid "Tassa kāye kāyānupassino viharato yo kāyasmiṃ chando so pahīyati."
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for the body."

msgctxt "sn47.37:1.5"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti."
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.37:2.1"
msgid ""
"Vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of feelings—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.37:2.2"
msgid "Tassa vedanāsu vedanānupassino viharato yo vedanāsu chando so pahīyati."
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for feelings."

msgctxt "sn47.37:2.3"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti."
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.182"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.37:3.1"
msgid ""
"Citte cittānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of the mind—keen, aware, and mindful, rid "
"of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.37:3.2"
msgid "Tassa citte cittānupassino viharato yo cittamhi chando so pahīyati."
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for the mind."

msgctxt "sn47.37:3.3"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hoti."
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn47.37:4.1"
msgid ""
"Dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, "
"rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn47.37:4.2"
msgid "Tassa dhammesu dhammānupassino viharato yo dhammesu chando so pahīyati."
msgstr "As they do so they give up desire for principles."

msgctxt "sn47.37:4.3"
msgid "Chandassa pahānā amataṃ sacchikataṃ hotī”ti."
msgstr "When desire is given up they realize the deathless.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn47.37:4.4"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
